items.text: too much flight outside off, drilled to sweeper cover for a single.
tossed up but down leg, the keeper fumbles as he can't get across, so in addition to it being a wide, they'll also scamper a bye.

steps out and brings his powerful wrists into play to whip this length ball against the turn from outside off. Bounces into the gap between wide long-on and deep midwicket. Superb from Liton, he knows what he's doing. Is happy to take the calculate gamble and at the moment, they're all paying off.
items.shortText: Mavuta to Liton Das, FOUR runs

items.text: sensibly dabs this into the off side for a quick single.
works this from outside off towards square leg.
worked into the gap at square leg for an easy single.
looks like he was ready to swing across the line but accounted for the dip and defended.
items.shortText: Williams to Liton Das, no run

items.text: cuts but straight to short third man
items.shortText: Williams to Liton Das, no run

items.text: whips this length ball from outside off towards deep square, loopy throw allows a second. Lazy work in the deep.
swept into the gap at deep square. Risky stuff, this was too full, he went across the stumps and picked the bones out of this with all his might.
items.shortText: Williams to Liton Das, FOUR runs

items.text: rocks back and pulls this into the gap at deep backward square again. Tripe bowling, too short, he opened up the leg side and powered the pull.
items.shortText: Williams to Liton Das, FOUR runs

items.text: looks to cut, but is beaten.
paddled to short fine leg
items.shortText: Mavuta to Imrul Kayes, no run

items.text: works this off his hip to deep square.
gets to the pitch of the ball and drives to sweeper cover.
stunning shot. Makes room, gets to the pitch and goes inside-out to clear extra cover. Bullet hit, exhilarating batting this.
items.shortText: Mavuta to Imrul Kayes, FOUR runs

items.text: short on middle and leg, pulled to deep square leg
slider, looks to turn to midwicket but gets an inside edge to square leg.
items.postText: It's time for drinks. Ground staff were out mopping up dew, which is pretty heavy. Unusual at this time of the year, according to Mohammad Isam. Also one of the reasons why the spinners haven't been able to grip the ball and haven't been able to get much turn off the surface.

items.text: short and sliding into middle and leg, he gets down on one knee and powers the pull to deep square leg
gets outside the line of the stumps and dabs into the off side for a quick single.
backs away to go over cover, drills this down to long-off off an inside edge.
shortish on middle and leg, whipped to deep midwicket

the man at deep midwicket was too far inside the boundary, and so when the pull arrived, he had to run across and leap to grab. This just eludes him and bounces away to the boundary. Poor ball but they could've yet been lucky, tonight doesn't seem to be Zimbabwe's night.

items.text: mistimes this cut to point.

items.text: short, slips this down leg and Imrul plays a superb short-am jab to beat deep square leg. In trying to put in the dive, the fielder ended up slipping and going over the ropes. Kyle Jarvis the fielder.
